    "faq": {
      "title": "Frequently Asked Questions",
      "q1": "What is a memory palace?",
      "a1": "A memory palace is an ancient memorization technique where you mentally place information at specific locations in a familiar space (like your home). When you need to recall, you mentally walk through that space and retrieve the information. XueBaOS uses AI to build these palaces for you automatically.",
      "q2": "Is this based on science?",
      "a2": "Yes! The method of loci (memory palace) has been used for over 2,500 years and is validated by modern cognitive science. Combined with FSRS (Free Spaced Repetition Scheduler) for optimal review timing, our approach is backed by research.",
      "q3": "What subjects does it work for?",
      "a3": "Any subject with factual content — biology, history, law, medicine, languages, chemistry, physics, mathematics (formulas), geography, and more. If you can write it down, XueBaOS can help you memorize it.",
      "q4": "Can I use it in Chinese?",
      "a4": "Absolutely! XueBaOS supports English, Traditional Chinese, and Simplified Chinese. Our AI understands both languages natively.",
      "q5": "Is there a free trial?",
      "a5": "The Free tier is free forever with generous limits. Try it out, build your first memory palace, and upgrade when you're ready for unlimited access."
    },
